(b) In a secondary school, 80 students played Hockey or Football. The number that played Football is 5 more than twice the number that played Hockey. If 15 students played both games and every student in the school plays at least one game. Find:
(i) the number of students that play football;
(ii) the number of students that play football but not Hockey;
(iii) the number of students that play Hockey but not Football. [5 marks]

(b) A load of mass 50 kg is placed in a lift. Calculate the reaction between the floor of the lift and the load when the lift:
(i) is moving at a constant speed;
(ii) moves upwards with an acceleration of 3 m/s². [5 marks]

(a) A 4 kg ball moving with a velocity of 10 m/s collides with a 16 kg ball moving with a velocity of 4 m/s in the opposite direction. Calculate the:
(i) velocity of the balls if they collide on impact;
(ii) loss energy resulting from the impact. [6 marks]
